Use this template for high performance scaling (replaces use of NPP)
when using ffmpeg 8 with cuda 13 :

./ffmpeg -hwaccel cuda -hwaccel_output_format cuda \
  -i input.mp4 \
  -vf "scale_cuda=1920:1080" \
  -c:v h264_nvenc \
  output.mp4


Verify ffmpeg is fully functional with hardware acceleration

./ffmpeg -filters | grep cuda
